1
00:01:42,065 --> 00:01:44,441
It's small!

2
00:01:58,206 --> 00:02:00,332
No, please. No!
Please!

3
00:02:00,583 --> 00:02:01,917
Davey!

4
00:02:02,377 --> 00:02:04,419
Come running, lad!

5
00:02:06,214 --> 00:02:09,383
- Stop!
- Brand you like a damn steer, bitch!

6
00:02:09,550 --> 00:02:13,720
- No. Please!
- Hold the bitch! Go on, hold her!

7
00:02:13,930 --> 00:02:17,307
Hold her, damn it!
I'll cut her tits off!

8
00:02:17,642 --> 00:02:19,643
Go get Skinny! Quick!

9
00:02:21,020 --> 00:02:22,354
Mike, don't!

10
00:02:27,902 --> 00:02:28,944
Skinny!

11
00:02:29,779 --> 00:02:31,405
Think it's funny?

12
00:02:32,991 --> 00:02:35,158
Skinny, get the gun!

13
00:02:45,628 --> 00:02:47,963
Get off of her, cowboy.

14
00:02:54,637 --> 00:02:57,264
- Wouldn't let you settle it?
- You know Skinny.

15
00:02:57,598 --> 00:03:00,892
He says he'll shoot them.
I says, "You can't. "

16
00:03:01,144 --> 00:03:04,563
He says, "Get Little Bill. "
I says, "He's sleeping. "

17
00:03:04,814 --> 00:03:08,483
He says he don't care.
He'll shoot them boys soon.

18
00:03:21,831 --> 00:03:23,457
She gonna die?

19
00:03:23,791 --> 00:03:25,500
She's gonna live.

20
00:03:27,587 --> 00:03:30,505
She didn't steal nothing
or touch his poke.

21
00:03:30,798 --> 00:03:33,425
When she seen
his teensy little pecker...

22
00:03:33,676 --> 00:03:37,804
... she giggled.
She didn't know no better.

23
00:03:40,016 --> 00:03:42,309
You can hang them, Little Bill.

24
00:04:02,872 --> 00:04:06,666
Step over to the office
and get the bullwhip.

25
00:04:07,126 --> 00:04:10,337
A whipping's all they get
after what they done?

26
00:04:12,673 --> 00:04:16,385
- It ain't no little thing, Alice.
- But what they done--

27
00:04:16,636 --> 00:04:18,136
Shut up!

28
00:04:21,057 --> 00:04:23,725
- Whipping ain't gonna settle this.
- No?

29
00:04:23,976 --> 00:04:29,022
Here's a contract between me
and Delilah Fitzgerald, the cut whore.

30
00:04:30,149 --> 00:04:33,693
I brought her from Boston,
paid her expenses and all.

31
00:04:34,195 --> 00:04:37,614
I got a contract that represents
an investment of capital.

32
00:04:37,907 --> 00:04:39,157
Property.

33
00:04:39,575 --> 00:04:41,201
Damaged property.

34
00:04:42,745 --> 00:04:45,038
Like if I hamstrung
one of their ponies.

35
00:04:46,541 --> 00:04:49,751
You think nobody'll fuck her now?

36
00:04:50,628 --> 00:04:52,045
Hell, no!

37
00:04:52,380 --> 00:04:54,089
Won't pay to do it.

38
00:04:54,424 --> 00:04:59,803
She can clean, but nobody's gonna pay
good money for a cut-up whore!

39
00:05:02,181 --> 00:05:06,518
You boys are off the Bar T.
Got your own string of ponies?

40
00:05:07,186 --> 00:05:09,271
Yeah, I got four.

41
00:05:11,899 --> 00:05:13,483
Six.

42
00:05:14,986 --> 00:05:17,737
You just as soon
not have a trial, no fuss?

43
00:05:18,448 --> 00:05:19,739
No, sir.

44
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:21,783
All right.

45
00:05:22,452 --> 00:05:24,077
You did the cutting.

46
00:05:24,412 --> 00:05:27,914
Come the fall, you bring in
five ponies to Skinny here.

47
00:05:28,583 --> 00:05:29,833
Five?

48
00:05:30,209 --> 00:05:32,919
And you!
You bring in two.

49
00:05:33,129 --> 00:05:35,255
- You give them over, hear?
- Yes, sir.

50
00:05:36,132 --> 00:05:38,800
Here's the bullwhip, Bill.

51
00:05:40,303 --> 00:05:42,304
Maybe we don't need this now.

52
00:05:43,931 --> 00:05:48,435
Let me tell you, come the spring,
Skinny don't have those ponies... .

53
00:05:49,645 --> 00:05:53,982
- I'll come looking for you.
- You ain't whipping them?

54
00:05:54,942 --> 00:05:57,068
I fined them instead, Alice.

55
00:05:57,361 --> 00:06:00,030
Skinny gets some ponies and that's it?!

56
00:06:01,657 --> 00:06:03,283
That ain't fair.

57
00:06:03,534 --> 00:06:04,868
That ain't fair!

58
00:06:12,168 --> 00:06:14,586
Haven't you seen
enough blood tonight?

59
00:06:18,466 --> 00:06:20,008
Hell, Alice!

60
00:06:21,135 --> 00:06:26,556
It ain't like they was tramps or
loafers or bad men. They were just...

61
00:06:26,807 --> 00:06:29,976
... hardworking boys that was foolish.

62
00:06:30,186 --> 00:06:34,147
- If they was given over to wickedness--
- Like whores?

63
00:06:36,067 --> 00:06:37,859
Tend to Delilah.

64
00:06:40,488 --> 00:06:42,113
Go ahead.

65
00:07:04,345 --> 00:07:05,929
I got $85.

66
00:07:06,180 --> 00:07:07,639
I don't know.

67
00:07:08,099 --> 00:07:11,393
If Delilah doesn't care,
why are we so riled up?

68
00:07:11,852 --> 00:07:15,313
Just because we let them fools
ride us like horses...

69
00:07:15,565 --> 00:07:19,025
... don't mean we let them
brand us like horses.

70
00:07:19,193 --> 00:07:24,281
Maybe we ain't nothing but whores,
but, by God, we ain't horses!

71
00:07:25,908 --> 00:07:28,243
I got $112.

72
00:07:29,412 --> 00:07:30,662
That's everything.

73
00:07:30,913 --> 00:07:33,623
How about you, Faith?

74
00:07:35,835 --> 00:07:37,877
Two hundred.

75
00:07:38,796 --> 00:07:41,172
Two hundred and forty dollars.

76
00:07:42,425 --> 00:07:44,718
Jesus, Faith!
What you been doing?

77
00:07:45,094 --> 00:07:48,638
Been giving Skinny something special?

78
00:07:52,393 --> 00:07:54,185
She laughed.

79
00:07:57,481 --> 00:08:01,276
With what Kate got, and Silky,
me and Little Sue--

80
00:08:01,569 --> 00:08:02,736
It ain't enough.

81
00:08:04,905 --> 00:08:06,448
Not yet, maybe.

82
00:08:47,031 --> 00:08:49,616
You don't look like no
rootin'-tootin'...

83
00:08:49,825 --> 00:08:53,036
... son of a bitching
cold-blooded assassin.

84
00:08:57,124 --> 00:08:58,375
Say what?

85
00:08:59,001 --> 00:09:03,254
My guess is you're calling yourself
Mr. William Munny.

86
00:09:03,839 --> 00:09:06,758
You have me confused
with someone else, mister.

87
00:09:07,218 --> 00:09:10,929
The same one who shot Charlie Pepper
in Lake County?

88
00:09:11,138 --> 00:09:12,681
Pa! Hey, Pa!

89
00:09:12,848 --> 00:09:14,349
What's up, son?

90
00:09:14,558 --> 00:09:16,559
Two more hogs got the fever.

91
00:09:17,186 --> 00:09:18,645
You shot Charlie Pepper.

92
00:09:18,854 --> 00:09:22,232
You killed William Harvey
and robbed that train in Missouri.

93
00:09:22,441 --> 00:09:23,733
Hold on, mister.

94
00:09:24,860 --> 00:09:27,654
Son, get those hogs separated there.

95
00:09:28,155 --> 00:09:29,781
Penny, help your brother.

96
00:09:30,074 --> 00:09:33,535
- That one's sick too?
- Yeah.

97
00:09:36,747 --> 00:09:38,665
We'll talk inside.

98
00:09:46,090 --> 00:09:49,050
So you're Pete Sothow's nephew?

99
00:09:50,219 --> 00:09:55,682
I thought you'd come to kill me for
something I'd done in the old days.

100
00:09:56,726 --> 00:09:59,352
I could have. Easy.

101
00:10:01,689 --> 00:10:03,857
I guess maybe so.

102
00:10:05,192 --> 00:10:10,321
You don't look like no meaner-than-hell,
cold-blooded damn killer.

103
00:10:11,449 --> 00:10:12,866
Maybe I ain't.

104
00:10:13,117 --> 00:10:17,495
Uncle Pete says you was the meanest
goddamn son of a bitch alive.

105
00:10:17,747 --> 00:10:22,542
And if I wanted a partner
for a killing, you were the worst one.

106
00:10:26,130 --> 00:10:27,881
Meaning the best.

107
00:10:28,299 --> 00:10:30,842
On account as you're as cold as snow...

108
00:10:31,093 --> 00:10:33,970
... and don't have
no weak nerve nor fear.

109
00:10:36,557 --> 00:10:38,266
Pete said that?

110
00:10:39,018 --> 00:10:41,603
Yeah, he did.

111
00:10:42,271 --> 00:10:44,147
I'm a killer myself, except...

112
00:10:44,398 --> 00:10:47,609
... I ain't killed as many as you
because of my youth.

113
00:10:47,860 --> 00:10:51,488
Schofield Kid,
that's what they call me.

114
00:10:53,574 --> 00:10:54,908
Why?

115
00:10:55,159 --> 00:10:57,410
You from Schofield?

116
00:10:57,787 --> 00:10:59,412
No, it's on account...

117
00:10:59,663 --> 00:11:03,124
... of my Schofield model
Smith & Wesson pistol.

118
00:11:08,005 --> 00:11:09,464
How about it, Will?

119
00:11:10,508 --> 00:11:12,050
How about what?

120
00:11:12,510 --> 00:11:14,761
How about being my partner?

121
00:11:15,179 --> 00:11:20,809
I'm heading north through Niobrara
to Wyoming to kill two no-good cowboys.

122
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:23,770
For what?

123
00:11:24,063 --> 00:11:28,024
For cutting up a lady.
Cut up her face.

124
00:11:28,317 --> 00:11:31,069
Cut her eyes out,
cut her ears off.

125
00:11:31,612 --> 00:11:34,322
They even cut her teats.

126
00:11:37,493 --> 00:11:38,785
Jesus.

127
00:11:39,620 --> 00:11:41,955
$1000 reward, Will.

128
00:11:43,332 --> 00:11:44,707
500 apiece.

129
00:11:48,712 --> 00:11:51,089
I can't move those damn pigs!

130
00:11:52,132 --> 00:11:55,718
Watch your cussing, will you?
Do the best you can with it.

131
00:11:55,970 --> 00:11:59,639
Then go to the pump
and get cleaned up. Come on.

132
00:12:05,688 --> 00:12:07,939
I ain't like that anymore, Kid.

133
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:12,861
It was whiskey done it
as much as anything else.

134
00:12:13,028 --> 00:12:15,321
I ain't had a drop in over 10 years.

135
00:12:15,865 --> 00:12:19,492
My wife, she cured me of that.

136
00:12:20,703 --> 00:12:23,955
Cured me of drinking and wickedness.

137
00:12:25,583 --> 00:12:27,834
You don't look so prosperous.

138
00:12:29,962 --> 00:12:33,006
You could buy her a new dress
with your half.

139
00:12:33,257 --> 00:12:37,886
- If we kill them, you can buy your--
- She's passed on.

140
00:12:38,345 --> 00:12:39,470
What?

141
00:12:42,016 --> 00:12:44,350
Been gone near 3 years now.

142
00:12:50,608 --> 00:12:55,445
Don't tell no one about the reward.
I don't need other gunmen collecting.

143
00:12:56,363 --> 00:12:58,197
We don't see no one out here.

144
00:12:59,992 --> 00:13:03,786
If you was to change your mind,
I'll be riding due west...

145
00:13:04,038 --> 00:13:06,289
... for the trail into Wyoming.

146
00:13:11,629 --> 00:13:15,006
Come on, let's separate those hogs.

147
00:13:44,495 --> 00:13:48,289
Two others.
I think they got the fever.

148
00:14:46,473 --> 00:14:48,391
Took you boys a while.

149
00:14:48,642 --> 00:14:52,979
A few more days and I was
gonna call on the sheriff.

150
00:14:53,230 --> 00:14:54,480
How about that?

151
00:14:54,732 --> 00:14:57,859
The river was all swelled up.
Couldn't cross it.

152
00:14:58,110 --> 00:15:00,903
I bet. Sleepy,
get them horses to the livery.

153
00:15:01,155 --> 00:15:03,781
Neil, take that one
over around the back.

154
00:15:11,373 --> 00:15:13,791
Now there's a beauty.

155
00:15:14,334 --> 00:15:17,128
You got two of mine.
This here one ain't yours.

156
00:15:17,379 --> 00:15:19,130
We'll see about that.

157
00:15:20,299 --> 00:15:23,217
Bastards!
Get out of town!

158
00:15:26,346 --> 00:15:28,598
Sick sons of bitches!

159
00:15:32,436 --> 00:15:35,521
- Don't come back, butcher!
- This here pony...

160
00:15:36,231 --> 00:15:39,108
... I brung for the lady my partner cut.

161
00:15:51,121 --> 00:15:52,538
She's the best.

162
00:15:57,836 --> 00:16:00,880
Better than the ones I gave him.

163
00:16:04,301 --> 00:16:06,052
She can sell her...

164
00:16:06,637 --> 00:16:08,346
... or do what she wants.

165
00:16:12,059 --> 00:16:16,813
A pony? She ain't got no face left,
you give her a mangy pony?

166
00:16:17,564 --> 00:16:19,148
She ain't mangy!

167
00:16:19,608 --> 00:16:21,818
Get out of here!

168
00:16:22,986 --> 00:16:25,404
We don't need your goddamn charity!

169
00:16:25,948 --> 00:16:28,574
Get out of our town
and don't come back!

170
00:16:30,702 --> 00:16:32,578
Get out of our town!

171
00:17:45,277 --> 00:17:48,279
Did Pa used to kill folks?

172
00:18:56,807 --> 00:19:00,184
I could tell your ma liked
those flowers I gave her.

173
00:19:00,435 --> 00:19:05,273
He ain't a saddle horse no more.
Ain't used to the feel.

174
00:19:05,482 --> 00:19:07,400
Take care of your sister, son.

175
00:19:07,651 --> 00:19:12,405
Kill a few chickens if you must.
Keep those hogs with the fever separate.

176
00:19:12,656 --> 00:19:17,368
If you have any problem, go see
Sally Two Trees at Ned Logan's.

177
00:19:42,477 --> 00:19:45,813
Ain't been in the saddle myself
in a while.

178
00:19:49,484 --> 00:19:53,195
She's getting even with me
for the sins of my youth.

179
00:19:53,447 --> 00:19:57,616
In my youth before I met
your dear departed ma...

180
00:19:57,868 --> 00:20:02,330
... I used to be weak
and given to mistreating animals.

181
00:20:06,793 --> 00:20:11,255
This horse and those hogs
over there...

182
00:20:14,134 --> 00:20:17,261
... are getting even
for the cruelty I inflicted.

183
00:20:17,512 --> 00:20:19,263
I used to be able to cuss...

184
00:20:19,514 --> 00:20:24,018
... and whip a horse, but your ma
showed me the error of my ways.

185
00:20:25,896 --> 00:20:28,147
I'll be back in two weeks.

186
00:20:28,315 --> 00:20:33,444
Remember the spirit of your dear
departed ma watches over you.

187
00:20:50,420 --> 00:20:53,339
- Where'd you get the money?
- We ain't got any!

188
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:56,926
- You told them cowboys you had!
- We was lying!

189
00:20:57,386 --> 00:20:59,053
Lying?

190
00:20:59,304 --> 00:21:02,890
What'll you do if somebody
comes to collect?

191
00:21:03,850 --> 00:21:06,769
You going to hump them
a thousand times?

192
00:21:09,898 --> 00:21:14,777
The kind of people who come for it
won't tolerate you not having it!

193
00:21:17,447 --> 00:21:20,491
They won't just cut up your face!

194
00:21:23,829 --> 00:21:26,038
You stupid bitches.

195
00:21:26,748 --> 00:21:28,707
You stupid bitches!

196
00:21:41,138 --> 00:21:42,263
Shit!

197
00:21:42,431 --> 00:21:44,974
Damn it! Jesus!

198
00:21:46,852 --> 00:21:48,185
Hit your finger?

199
00:21:50,689 --> 00:21:52,231
Hello, Skinny.

200
00:21:52,774 --> 00:21:54,692
Damn, you snuck up on me.

201
00:21:55,402 --> 00:21:57,528
What do you think of her?

202
00:21:57,779 --> 00:22:00,322
I heard you done the roof yourself.

203
00:22:00,574 --> 00:22:05,161
Roof? Jesus, I did practically
the whole damn thing myself.

204
00:22:05,412 --> 00:22:09,290
The Roberts boy carried wood for me,
but that's all.

205
00:22:09,541 --> 00:22:11,417
What is all that wood?

206
00:22:11,710 --> 00:22:15,463
I'm building a porch
so I can sit of an evening...

207
00:22:15,714 --> 00:22:20,259
... and smoke my pipe and drink coffee
and watch the sunset.

208
00:22:23,180 --> 00:22:25,848
Came out here just
to take a look at her?

209
00:22:26,099 --> 00:22:28,100
- Them whores!
- Yeah?

210
00:22:28,351 --> 00:22:33,814
Been humping them cowboys
who been in town the last two weeks.

211
00:22:34,107 --> 00:22:35,733
Shit, Skinny.

212
00:22:37,444 --> 00:22:40,362
We got railroad barons.
We got cattle barons.

213
00:22:40,614 --> 00:22:43,449
You'll be the first billiard baron.

214
00:22:43,658 --> 00:22:47,620
They been humping and telling
every bowlegged one of them...

215
00:22:47,871 --> 00:22:50,873
... they'll pay $1000 to whoever...

216
00:22:51,124 --> 00:22:54,126
... kills the two boys
that cut up Delilah.

217
00:22:56,338 --> 00:23:00,591
Those cowboys are riding that beef
down to Kansas and Cheyenne?

218
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:10,017
All week long?

219
00:23:10,310 --> 00:23:12,770
I didn't hear till last night myself.

220
00:23:13,396 --> 00:23:17,066
The word's probably got all the way
to Texas by now.

221
00:23:18,193 --> 00:23:21,612
Nobody'll come clear from Texas.

222
00:23:22,781 --> 00:23:24,573
You sure they got that money?

223
00:23:25,075 --> 00:23:30,329
Women can lie. Asked where the
money is, they say they got none.

224
00:23:30,580 --> 00:23:34,875
But those five could have
squirreled it away. Maybe.

225
00:23:37,963 --> 00:23:39,547
That much?

226
00:23:41,007 --> 00:23:43,801
You could run off them two cowboys.

227
00:23:43,969 --> 00:23:46,971
I could run off them whores.

228
00:23:48,890 --> 00:23:51,809
They'll just up and run anyhow,
them two.

229
00:23:55,730 --> 00:23:58,065
They'll stay out at the Bar T.

230
00:23:58,817 --> 00:24:00,943
Close to their friends.

231
00:24:02,070 --> 00:24:05,155
Shit, could be nobody
won't come at all.

232
00:24:07,659 --> 00:24:09,910
Got to go.
I like your house.

233
00:24:44,446 --> 00:24:46,530
Well, I'll be... .

234
00:24:47,741 --> 00:24:49,366
It's Will!

235
00:24:55,999 --> 00:25:01,629
Come in the house out of the sun.
Sally, see to Will's horse.

236
00:25:06,801 --> 00:25:08,969
What are you doing here?

237
00:25:09,137 --> 00:25:12,389
Just thought I'd drop in on you.

238
00:25:13,058 --> 00:25:15,643
We ain't bad men no more.

239
00:25:15,977 --> 00:25:17,645
We're farmers.

240
00:25:18,063 --> 00:25:22,858
Should be easy killing them,
if they don't go on down to Texas.

241
00:25:24,319 --> 00:25:28,572
How long since you fired a gun
at a man? Nine, ten years?

242
00:25:30,742 --> 00:25:32,326
Eleven.

243
00:25:33,828 --> 00:25:35,079
Easy, huh?

244
00:25:36,081 --> 00:25:39,166
I don't know it was
all that easy even back then.

245
00:25:39,501 --> 00:25:42,294
And we was young and full of beans.

246
00:25:42,504 --> 00:25:44,588
If you was mad at them...

247
00:25:45,256 --> 00:25:47,966
... over some wrong,
I could see shooting them.

248
00:25:48,635 --> 00:25:51,345
We done stuff for money before.

249
00:25:54,891 --> 00:25:57,017
We thought we did.

250
00:25:57,268 --> 00:26:00,312
What'd these fellows do?
Cheat at cards?

251
00:26:00,563 --> 00:26:04,108
Steal some strays?
Spit on a rich fellow? What?

252
00:26:04,484 --> 00:26:05,901
They cut up a woman.

253
00:26:06,277 --> 00:26:07,569
What?

254
00:26:08,947 --> 00:26:14,159
Cut up her face, cut her eyes out,
cut her fingers off, cut her tits.

255
00:26:15,870 --> 00:26:18,205
Everything but her cunny,
I suppose.

256
00:26:20,041 --> 00:26:21,625
I'll be dogged.

257
00:26:26,131 --> 00:26:27,965
Guess they got it coming.

258
00:26:29,551 --> 00:26:31,051
Of course, Will...

259
00:26:32,303 --> 00:26:36,348
... if Claudia was alive,
you wouldn't do this.

260
00:26:45,650 --> 00:26:48,527
Could you look in on my youngsters
next week?

261
00:26:48,778 --> 00:26:51,655
They got some hogs
they're trying to separate.

262
00:26:53,825 --> 00:26:56,744
How long you reckon you're gonna be?

263
00:26:58,246 --> 00:26:59,747
Two weeks, I guess.

264
00:27:11,760 --> 00:27:13,343
What's this Kid like?

265
00:27:16,514 --> 00:27:17,806
Three ways?

266
00:27:19,851 --> 00:27:22,603
I see you still have
that Spencer rifle.

267
00:27:24,689 --> 00:27:28,942
And I can still knock the eye
out of a bird flying too.

268
00:27:37,368 --> 00:27:38,911
Jesus, Will!

269
00:28:36,094 --> 00:28:38,428
He must be moving right along.

270
00:28:38,596 --> 00:28:42,432
We'll come across him
tomorrow, I reckon.

271
00:28:53,027 --> 00:28:54,945
Kind of got used to my bed.

272
00:28:55,196 --> 00:28:58,615
This ain't going to be like no home.

273
00:28:58,783 --> 00:29:01,535
That ain't the only thing I'll miss.

274
00:29:07,083 --> 00:29:08,417
Hell, I'm sorry.

275
00:29:09,043 --> 00:29:12,546
Don't fret it.
It ain't nothing.

276
00:29:14,883 --> 00:29:18,677
She don't like it much,
you riding off with me.

277
00:29:19,679 --> 00:29:21,513
Gave me the evil eye.

278
00:29:25,476 --> 00:29:27,728
You know, Sally's injun...

279
00:29:28,605 --> 00:29:30,772
... and injuns ain't over-friendly.

280
00:29:32,984 --> 00:29:34,401
I don't blame her.

281
00:29:35,820 --> 00:29:37,738
I won't hold it against her.

282
00:29:37,989 --> 00:29:39,907
She knew me back then.

283
00:29:40,491 --> 00:29:41,909
She knew what a...

284
00:29:42,493 --> 00:29:44,912
... no-good son of a bitch I was.

285
00:29:46,748 --> 00:29:49,333
She ain't allowing that I changed.

286
00:29:50,168 --> 00:29:52,920
She don't realize I ain't
like that no more.

287
00:29:53,171 --> 00:29:55,505
- You know, Will--
- I ain't the same.

288
00:29:57,008 --> 00:30:01,762
Claudia straightened me up.
Cleared me of drinking whiskey and all.

289
00:30:03,181 --> 00:30:04,890
Going on this killing...

290
00:30:05,141 --> 00:30:08,226
... don't mean I'll go back
to the way I was.

291
00:30:09,604 --> 00:30:11,271
Just need the money.

292
00:30:11,773 --> 00:30:15,192
Get a new start for them youngsters.

293
00:30:19,864 --> 00:30:22,699
Remember that drover
I shot in the mouth...

294
00:30:22,867 --> 00:30:26,036
... and his teeth came
out the back of his head?

295
00:30:28,373 --> 00:30:31,541
I think about him now and again.

296
00:30:33,628 --> 00:30:37,130
He didn't do anything
to deserve to get shot.

297
00:30:37,298 --> 00:30:41,176
At least nothing I remembered
when I sobered up.

298
00:30:45,390 --> 00:30:47,975
You was one crazy son of a bitch.

299
00:30:51,229 --> 00:30:54,189
No one liked me,
and the boys all thought...

300
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:58,193
... I'd shoot them
out of pure meanness.

301
00:30:59,487 --> 00:31:01,405
You ain't like that no more.

302
00:31:02,323 --> 00:31:04,491
Eagle, he hated my guts.

303
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:08,870
Bonaparte didn't think too much of me.

304
00:31:09,330 --> 00:31:11,081
Quincy neither, I reckon.

305
00:31:13,501 --> 00:31:16,503
Quincy used to just watch
all the time...

306
00:31:17,922 --> 00:31:19,423
... scared.

307
00:31:20,591 --> 00:31:22,092
Like I said...

308
00:31:23,594 --> 00:31:26,346
... you ain't like that no more.

309
00:31:26,514 --> 00:31:27,848
That's right.

310
00:31:29,434 --> 00:31:31,351
I'm just a fellow now.

311
00:31:31,602 --> 00:31:34,438
I ain't no different
than anyone else...

312
00:31:35,189 --> 00:31:36,440
... no more.

313
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:56,835
What son of a bitch shot him?
Was it one of them John Bulls?

314
00:31:57,086 --> 00:32:01,590
No, sir. The would-be assassin
is a gentleman of French ancestry.

315
00:32:01,841 --> 00:32:05,635
Or so it seems.
I don't wish to give offense...

316
00:32:05,887 --> 00:32:09,806
... but the French are known
to be a race of assassins...

317
00:32:10,058 --> 00:32:12,059
... who can't shoot worth a damn.

318
00:32:12,310 --> 00:32:15,979
Any Frenchmen present
are excluded, of course.

319
00:32:16,230 --> 00:32:20,984
Says here a fellow by the name
of Guiteau. G-U-L-T--

320
00:32:21,235 --> 00:32:24,905
Sure as hell sounds
like a John Bull to me.

321
00:32:25,323 --> 00:32:30,952
Again, I don't wish to give offense
when I suggest this country select...

322
00:32:31,204 --> 00:32:35,499
... a king or even a queen,
rather than a president.

323
00:32:37,460 --> 00:32:40,462
One isn't that quick
to shoot a king or a queen.

324
00:32:40,630 --> 00:32:43,173
The majesty of royalty, you see.

325
00:32:46,260 --> 00:32:49,179
Maybe you don't wish
to give offense, sir...

326
00:32:49,472 --> 00:32:51,598
... but you are giving it pretty thick.

327
00:32:52,016 --> 00:32:54,768
This country don't need
no queens whatsoever.

328
00:32:55,103 --> 00:32:57,771
- When I heard about queens--
- Shut up, Joe.

329
00:32:58,022 --> 00:33:00,774
What's wrong with you, Thirsty?
This dude--

330
00:33:01,025 --> 00:33:03,902
Might be that this dude
is English Bob.

331
00:33:04,904 --> 00:33:07,948
Works for the railroad
shooting Chinamen.

332
00:33:08,199 --> 00:33:12,035
Might be he's waiting for some cowboy
to touch his pistol...

333
00:33:12,286 --> 00:33:13,912
... so he can shoot him.

334
00:33:25,716 --> 00:33:28,301
Is that a fact, mister?

335
00:33:28,469 --> 00:33:30,220
You English Bob?

336
00:33:32,849 --> 00:33:34,516
Pheasants.

337
00:33:36,310 --> 00:33:38,311
Let's shoot some pheasants.

338
00:33:38,563 --> 00:33:39,813
Ten shots.

339
00:33:40,148 --> 00:33:42,816
At, let's say, $1 a pheasant.

340
00:33:43,484 --> 00:33:46,653
I'll shoot for the queen, and you...

341
00:33:47,071 --> 00:33:48,655
... for whomever.

342
00:34:05,089 --> 00:34:10,427
That's eight for me and one for you.
That comes to seven American dollars.

343
00:34:10,595 --> 00:34:13,013
Pretty damn good shooting...

344
00:34:13,181 --> 00:34:14,931
... for a John Bull.

345
00:34:15,433 --> 00:34:19,769
No doubt your aim was
affected by your grief...

346
00:34:20,605 --> 00:34:24,107
... over the injury to your president.

347
00:34:35,286 --> 00:34:39,497
It's the climate that does it.
That, and the infernal distances.

348
00:34:39,665 --> 00:34:40,749
Does what?

349
00:34:41,125 --> 00:34:44,211
Induces people to shoot
persons in high places.

350
00:34:49,759 --> 00:34:52,469
That's the second one shot
in 20 years.

351
00:34:52,678 --> 00:34:56,056
It's uncivilized shooting
persons of substance.

352
00:35:53,197 --> 00:35:54,447
Thank you.

353
00:35:57,201 --> 00:35:58,618
Pardon me, gentlemen.

354
00:36:00,955 --> 00:36:06,376
The law obliges you to surrender
sidearms to the proper authorities.

355
00:36:07,378 --> 00:36:08,670
Proper authority?

356
00:36:11,799 --> 00:36:17,220
I assure you that neither my companion
or I carry firearms on our person.

357
00:36:17,805 --> 00:36:21,599
We rely upon the goodwill
of our fellow man...

358
00:36:21,851 --> 00:36:24,227
... and the forbearance of reptiles.

359
00:36:37,742 --> 00:36:39,492
Unarmed, my ass!

360
00:36:40,703 --> 00:36:41,953
Christ, it's hot!

361
00:36:42,204 --> 00:36:46,791
If I'm going to get shot,
I'd rather it was hot than cold.

362
00:36:47,043 --> 00:36:51,171
Everything hurts more when it's cold.
You know how if you hit--

363
00:36:51,422 --> 00:36:52,630
Shut up, Fatty!

364
00:36:54,759 --> 00:36:56,259
Clyde's back.

365
00:36:56,510 --> 00:36:58,386
- With Little Bill?
- No.

366
00:36:59,138 --> 00:37:00,221
Shit!

367
00:37:05,644 --> 00:37:08,438
- You clean my Remington?
- Cleaned and loaded.

368
00:37:09,607 --> 00:37:11,483
Where's Little Bill?

369
00:37:11,984 --> 00:37:13,610
Building his damn porch.

370
00:37:14,028 --> 00:37:15,695
Building his porch?

371
00:37:16,238 --> 00:37:19,616
If you got shot,
would you want it to be hot or cold?

372
00:37:19,909 --> 00:37:21,618
I ain't gonna get shot.

373
00:37:23,579 --> 00:37:24,704
He's coming?

374
00:37:25,581 --> 00:37:27,499
Of course he's coming.

375
00:37:28,292 --> 00:37:29,709
I just loaded that.

376
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:34,172
I don't trust nobody loading my guns
before a shooting.

377
00:37:34,548 --> 00:37:35,548
What'd he say?

378
00:37:35,966 --> 00:37:39,010
Little Bill said he was building
his porch.

379
00:37:39,804 --> 00:37:42,597
- You seen that thing?
- It was all loaded.

380
00:37:42,848 --> 00:37:46,267
Clyde, you got three pistols
and you only got one arm!

381
00:37:46,936 --> 00:37:50,897
I don't want to get killed
for lack of shooting back.

382
00:37:52,733 --> 00:37:55,777
He don't have a straight
angle on that whole porch!

383
00:37:56,237 --> 00:38:00,740
Or the whole house, for that matter!
He is the worst damn carpenter.

384
00:38:01,450 --> 00:38:03,076
He didn't say nothing?

385
00:38:03,953 --> 00:38:06,788
Asked what they looked like.

386
00:38:07,498 --> 00:38:10,250
Maybe he's tough,
but he ain't no carpenter.

387
00:38:10,751 --> 00:38:12,544
Maybe he ain't so tough.

388
00:38:13,754 --> 00:38:16,464
Seem like he was scared?

389
00:38:17,341 --> 00:38:19,384
Little Bill? Him scared?

390
00:38:20,678 --> 00:38:23,888
We never seen him up
against any like these ones.

391
00:38:24,181 --> 00:38:26,182
Killers.

392
00:38:26,517 --> 00:38:30,186
Little Bill come out of Kansas
and Texas, boys.

393
00:38:30,354 --> 00:38:32,397
He worked them tough towns.

394
00:38:32,731 --> 00:38:34,065
Just wondered.

395
00:38:36,068 --> 00:38:37,944
Anybody could be scared.

396
00:38:43,033 --> 00:38:44,951
He wasn't scared, boys.

397
00:38:46,203 --> 00:38:49,164
He just ain't no carpenter.

398
00:38:53,919 --> 00:38:56,212
There's a dignity in royalty...

399
00:38:56,464 --> 00:38:59,591
... which precludes
the likelihood of assassination.

400
00:38:59,842 --> 00:39:01,384
If you pointed a pistol...

401
00:39:01,635 --> 00:39:04,929
... at a monarch,
your hands would shake as if palsied.

402
00:39:05,181 --> 00:39:08,725
I wouldn't point no pistol at nobody.

403
00:39:08,893 --> 00:39:10,810
That's a wise policy.

404
00:39:11,729 --> 00:39:15,231
But if you did, I assure you,
the sight of royalty...

405
00:39:15,483 --> 00:39:20,195
... would cause you to dismiss thoughts
of bloodshed. You would stand--

406
00:39:20,446 --> 00:39:23,781
How shall I put it?
In awe.

407
00:39:26,535 --> 00:39:31,498
A president... . 
Why not shoot a president?

408
00:39:37,254 --> 00:39:38,671
Keep the change.

409
00:39:38,923 --> 00:39:42,675
This Strawberry Alice person,
tell me again.

410
00:39:42,927 --> 00:39:46,679
Down the street to Greely's Beer
Garden and Billiards Parlor.

411
00:39:47,056 --> 00:39:49,474
Say you want a game of billiards.

412
00:39:49,725 --> 00:39:53,019
Billiards? Even though
I don't really wish to play?

413
00:39:53,312 --> 00:39:57,106
No matter. They burned the table
in '78 for firewood.

414
00:39:57,775 --> 00:39:59,359
Quite right.

415
00:40:00,653 --> 00:40:03,321
Mr. Beauchamp,
I think a cup of tea--

416
00:40:18,420 --> 00:40:19,671
Hello, Bob.

417
00:40:22,341 --> 00:40:24,842
Boys, this here is English Bob.

418
00:40:26,345 --> 00:40:28,263
Shit and fried eggs.

419
00:40:30,849 --> 00:40:32,350
Been a long time.

420
00:40:33,686 --> 00:40:35,103
Run out of Chinamen?

421
00:40:37,314 --> 00:40:39,732
I thought that you were dead.

422
00:40:40,859 --> 00:40:43,319
You've shaved your chin whiskers off.

423
00:40:44,238 --> 00:40:47,907
I was tasting the soup
two hours after I ate it.

424
00:40:48,325 --> 00:40:51,578
Actually, what I heard was,
you fell off your horse...

425
00:40:51,745 --> 00:40:53,246
... drunk, of course.

426
00:40:53,539 --> 00:40:56,124
And that you broke your bloody neck.

427
00:40:57,668 --> 00:40:59,794
I heard that one myself, Bob.

428
00:40:59,962 --> 00:41:01,879
Hell, I even thought I was dead.

429
00:41:02,172 --> 00:41:05,425
Till I found out
I was just in Nebraska.

430
00:41:06,385 --> 00:41:07,468
Who's he?

431
00:41:08,220 --> 00:41:09,470
W. W. Beauchamp.

432
00:41:10,723 --> 00:41:14,058
This is Little Bill Daggett.

433
00:41:14,226 --> 00:41:16,269
And friends, of course.

434
00:41:17,354 --> 00:41:19,814
From Newton, Hays? From Abilene?

435
00:41:20,566 --> 00:41:22,317
In person.

436
00:41:23,694 --> 00:41:25,987
You work for the railroads too?

437
00:41:28,073 --> 00:41:29,157
I write.

438
00:41:30,242 --> 00:41:31,284
Letters?

439
00:41:31,744 --> 00:41:33,494
Books, Bill. Books.

440
00:41:34,580 --> 00:41:35,663
Actually...

441
00:41:36,248 --> 00:41:38,708
... he's my biographer.

442
00:41:44,423 --> 00:41:46,841
I wouldn't do that if I were you.

443
00:41:54,725 --> 00:41:56,184
It's only a book.

444
00:41:56,769 --> 00:41:57,810
A book?

445
00:42:04,193 --> 00:42:06,653
That means you boys can read.

446
00:42:06,820 --> 00:42:12,659
That means you saw the signs outside
town saying surrender your firearms.

447
00:42:14,745 --> 00:42:18,081
But like you told young Andy...

448
00:42:18,540 --> 00:42:21,626
... you're not armed, are you?

449
00:42:21,794 --> 00:42:23,378
Not really, Bill.

450
00:42:24,755 --> 00:42:28,383
Got a Peacemaker, but that
wouldn't worry you, would it?

451
00:42:28,759 --> 00:42:32,887
If you don't see it.
Or better, if you don't hear it.

452
00:42:33,472 --> 00:42:35,181
I'm afraid so, Bob.

453
00:42:35,974 --> 00:42:39,018
I don't like firearms around.

454
00:42:59,957 --> 00:43:02,625
Be very careful with it, sonny.

455
00:43:08,173 --> 00:43:11,509
See what kind of books
Mr. Beauchamp is packing.

456
00:43:15,681 --> 00:43:18,516
Make sure you don't get wet.

457
00:43:24,606 --> 00:43:25,857
No shit.

458
00:43:26,108 --> 00:43:29,527
All he's got is writing
stuff and this book.

459
00:43:32,281 --> 00:43:33,865
The Duck of Death?

460
00:43:34,116 --> 00:43:35,408
Duke.

461
00:43:37,161 --> 00:43:38,578
"The Duke. "

462
00:43:41,749 --> 00:43:43,750
Good afternoon, gentlemen.

463
00:43:44,001 --> 00:43:46,127
I'll have that. 32, Bob.

464
00:43:59,266 --> 00:44:00,933
Now, Little Bill...

465
00:44:01,643 --> 00:44:04,937
... you will leave me at the mercy
of my enemies.

466
00:44:09,693 --> 00:44:11,235
Enemies?

467
00:44:14,323 --> 00:44:17,992
You been talking about the queen again?

468
00:44:18,160 --> 00:44:19,410
On Independence Day?

469
00:44:32,508 --> 00:44:35,551
I guess you think I'm kicking you.

470
00:44:35,969 --> 00:44:37,428
But it ain't so!

471
00:44:37,846 --> 00:44:39,722
What I'm doing is talking!

472
00:44:40,390 --> 00:44:43,851
You hear?!
Talking to all them villains in Kansas!

473
00:44:44,102 --> 00:44:46,604
To all those villains in Missouri!

474
00:44:54,363 --> 00:44:55,613
And those villains...

475
00:44:57,032 --> 00:44:58,908
... down in Cheyenne!

476
00:45:04,706 --> 00:45:08,709
I'm saying there ain't no whore's gold!

477
00:45:12,881 --> 00:45:17,051
Even if there was,
they wouldn't want to come for it...

478
00:45:17,261 --> 00:45:18,302
... anyhow!

479
00:45:47,541 --> 00:45:50,543
What are you all looking at?!
Go on!

480
00:45:57,926 --> 00:45:59,844
Mind your own business!

481
00:46:28,874 --> 00:46:30,249
Ever go into town?

482
00:46:31,501 --> 00:46:35,379
On occasion.
To sell a hog, pick up supplies.

483
00:46:36,965 --> 00:46:39,175
I mean, get yourself a woman.

484
00:46:42,554 --> 00:46:44,931
No, I never go into town for that.

485
00:46:45,098 --> 00:46:46,891
A man like me?

486
00:46:47,935 --> 00:46:51,520
Only woman I could get
is one I'd have to pay for.

487
00:46:52,189 --> 00:46:54,440
That ain't right, buying flesh.

488
00:46:56,026 --> 00:46:59,528
Claudia, rest her soul,
wouldn't want me doing that...

489
00:46:59,780 --> 00:47:01,238
... me being a father.

490
00:47:06,495 --> 00:47:09,121
You just use your hand?

491
00:47:13,835 --> 00:47:16,462
I don't miss it all that much.

492
00:47:37,275 --> 00:47:39,485
Goddamn!
Somebody's shooting at us!

493
00:47:39,653 --> 00:47:42,279
Shit. Did it hit you?

494
00:47:44,533 --> 00:47:48,077
I bumped my head
falling off my horse.

495
00:47:52,374 --> 00:47:54,291
Ain't shooting at us no more.

496
00:47:56,712 --> 00:47:58,462
Shooting way over yonder.

497
00:48:00,716 --> 00:48:03,217
What the hell's he shooting at?

498
00:48:03,385 --> 00:48:06,137
Beats the hell out of me.

499
00:48:08,306 --> 00:48:10,474
Reckon we in somebody's field?

500
00:48:10,726 --> 00:48:13,519
I didn't see nothing planted.

501
00:48:13,687 --> 00:48:15,146
Shooting at us again.

502
00:48:19,693 --> 00:48:22,111
He's shooting at the whole horizon.

503
00:48:23,321 --> 00:48:24,989
Wait! You'll mark us!

504
00:48:25,240 --> 00:48:26,490
Hey, Kid!

505
00:48:28,827 --> 00:48:32,496
- That's the Kid shooting at us?
- Kid, it's me! Will Munny!

506
00:48:32,748 --> 00:48:35,082
What's he shooting at us for?

507
00:48:35,333 --> 00:48:36,584
Is that you?

508
00:48:39,337 --> 00:48:40,671
Yeah, it's me!

509
00:48:41,214 --> 00:48:44,341
Don't go shooting at us no more!
You hear me?

