like they was bad men.

756
01:10:36,403 --> 01:10:40,365
But without any sand or character.
Not even any bad character.

757
01:10:43,869 --> 01:10:46,996
I do not like assassins.

758
01:10:47,790 --> 01:10:50,291
Or men of low character.

759
01:10:51,627 --> 01:10:53,336
Like your friend, English Bob.

760
01:10:54,004 --> 01:10:56,005
But, now Bob was no coward.

761
01:10:56,256 --> 01:10:59,467
He wouldn't cry
and carry on like that--

762
01:11:00,844 --> 01:11:01,886
Sheriff... .

763
01:11:03,180 --> 01:11:05,848
I don't have any more receptacles.

764
01:11:06,266 --> 01:11:09,685
Maybe you should hang the carpenter.

765
01:11:10,479 --> 01:11:11,687
What?

766
01:11:14,024 --> 01:11:18,444
I was just saying because of the... . 
You hang... .

767
01:11:19,196 --> 01:11:20,530
Doesn't matter.

768
01:11:22,991 --> 01:11:24,784
What the hell?

769
01:11:25,369 --> 01:11:27,203
On a night like this!

770
01:11:28,539 --> 01:11:32,542
- Who the hell is it?
- Deputy Charley Hecker, Bill.

771
01:11:36,171 --> 01:11:40,633
Three fellows just come into town.
They're down to Greely's.

772
01:11:40,801 --> 01:11:43,219
At least two of them got guns.

773
01:11:50,894 --> 01:11:53,479
What the hell's keeping that Kid?

774
01:11:55,149 --> 01:11:57,066
You don't suppose he's up--

775
01:11:58,402 --> 01:12:00,027
Jesus, Will!

776
01:12:00,362 --> 01:12:01,737
You look like shit.

777
01:12:06,410 --> 01:12:09,078
You remember Eagle Hendershot?

778
01:12:13,709 --> 01:12:15,334
I saw him.

779
01:12:16,879 --> 01:12:18,254
Will, he's dead.

780
01:12:19,173 --> 01:12:21,007
No, I saw him, Ned.

781
01:12:21,842 --> 01:12:25,511
His head was broke open.
You could see inside of it.

782
01:12:27,055 --> 01:12:30,016
Jesus! You got a fever.

783
01:12:30,267 --> 01:12:33,603
- Take a drink, will you?
- Worms were coming out.

784
01:12:36,690 --> 01:12:39,775
Look, I'm going up to see
what's keeping the Kid.

785
01:12:40,110 --> 01:12:44,572
Must be getting an advance
from one of the sporting ladies.

786
01:12:46,867 --> 01:12:48,284
If I was to... .

787
01:12:50,204 --> 01:12:55,791
If it worked out that I could take
a little time for myself... .

788
01:12:56,710 --> 01:12:59,086
I mean you wouldn't... .

789
01:13:01,882 --> 01:13:04,926
I guess you wouldn't want to come.

790
01:14:26,508 --> 01:14:28,217
Give me the pistol.

791
01:14:34,516 --> 01:14:37,727
I says give me over your pistol.

792
01:14:40,188 --> 01:14:41,564
I ain't drunk.

793
01:14:43,817 --> 01:14:48,154
Ordinance says you got to turn in
your firearms to my office...

794
01:14:48,322 --> 01:14:49,572
... day or night.

795
01:14:56,496 --> 01:15:01,584
I guess you didn't see the sign,
because of the weather.

796
01:15:01,835 --> 01:15:02,918
No.

797
01:15:04,254 --> 01:15:05,755
But I ain't... .

798
01:15:06,548 --> 01:15:08,049
I ain't armed.

799
01:15:08,842 --> 01:15:13,262
What about your friends upstairs?
They got any pistols?

800
01:15:17,559 --> 01:15:19,352
They ain't armed either.

801
01:15:21,271 --> 01:15:22,772
Spilled your whiskey.

802
01:15:24,858 --> 01:15:26,275
What's your name?

803
01:15:28,195 --> 01:15:29,445
William...

804
01:15:32,157 --> 01:15:33,282
... Hendershot.

805
01:15:37,079 --> 01:15:39,455
Well, Mr. William Hendershot...

806
01:15:41,583 --> 01:15:46,712
... what if I was to say you was
a no-good son of a bitch and a liar?

807
01:15:48,298 --> 01:15:53,469
And if I was to say you shit in your
pants because of a cowardly soul...

808
01:15:53,637 --> 01:15:58,808
... I bet you'd show me that pistol
quick and kill me. Isn't that so?

809
01:16:05,565 --> 01:16:07,733
Maybe, yeah, I guess.

810
01:16:09,444 --> 01:16:10,820
But the fact is...

811
01:16:11,405 --> 01:16:14,615
... I ain't carrying no firearm.

812
01:16:14,991 --> 01:16:16,325
Get up.

813
01:16:49,276 --> 01:16:51,527
What's this for,
snakes and such?

814
01:16:53,864 --> 01:16:57,700
We don't have any snakes in here,
Mr. Hendershot.

815
01:17:02,038 --> 01:17:06,375
It ain't loaded or... . 
Powder's wet.

816
01:17:09,671 --> 01:17:11,255
You see, Mr. Beauchamp?

817
01:17:14,384 --> 01:17:17,052
This is the trash
I was speaking of!

818
01:17:24,561 --> 01:17:28,647
They're in all the saloons
in all your prosperous communities!

819
01:17:28,815 --> 01:17:29,899
Wichita!

820
01:17:33,028 --> 01:17:35,029
Over in Cheyenne!

821
01:17:38,241 --> 01:17:39,492
Abilene!

822
01:17:43,330 --> 01:17:47,082
But not in the town of Big Whiskey.

823
01:17:50,587 --> 01:17:53,339
Hurry up!
You know what to tell Bill.

824
01:17:53,590 --> 01:17:57,426
Look for that lone pine.
Miss the pine, you won't find it.

825
01:17:57,677 --> 01:17:59,804
Forget the shirt!
Put the boots on!

826
01:18:09,940 --> 01:18:13,692
- What are we going to do about Will?
- Come on, Kid!

827
01:18:13,944 --> 01:18:17,196
Let's hope them horses are still there!

828
01:18:50,564 --> 01:18:52,648
Let the man out, W. W.

829
01:18:53,441 --> 01:18:57,653
He's desiring to leave the hospitality
of Big Whiskey behind him.

830
01:19:30,896 --> 01:19:32,021
Easy!

831
01:19:32,272 --> 01:19:36,775
- She's got to turn a dollar a time.
- Why'd they lit out the back window?

832
01:19:37,027 --> 01:19:39,528
They seen you beating on their friend.

833
01:19:40,530 --> 01:19:45,117
- They come for the billiards, honest.
- Billiards?!

834
01:19:45,827 --> 01:19:49,705
- They were just passing through?
- They was going to Fort Buford.

835
01:19:50,040 --> 01:19:52,917
You kicked the shit
out of an innocent man.

836
01:19:53,543 --> 01:19:54,877
Innocent?

837
01:19:55,211 --> 01:19:56,545
Innocent of what?

838
01:20:23,949 --> 01:20:27,743
Jesus, Ned! You done this before?

839
01:20:28,995 --> 01:20:30,496
Plenty of times.

840
01:20:32,207 --> 01:20:34,375
His pistol must've jammed.

841
01:20:36,753 --> 01:20:40,381
Here. Bring that candle in closer.
I can't see.

842
01:20:51,935 --> 01:20:55,938
He wouldn't take no beating
if it hadn't jammed.

843
01:20:56,106 --> 01:20:58,732
He wouldn't give it over
and not shoot.

844
01:21:02,779 --> 01:21:04,530
He don't look so good.

845
01:21:06,741 --> 01:21:08,534
He didn't even pull his pistol?

846
01:21:08,785 --> 01:21:12,538
- He ain't as tough as you, Kid.
- I'd have pulled my pistol.

847
01:21:12,789 --> 01:21:15,791
You did!
Out of the lady and out the window!

848
01:21:16,042 --> 01:21:19,044
- That was your idea! l--
- We got to go.

849
01:21:19,379 --> 01:21:22,423
What? I'm ready for another advance.

850
01:21:22,632 --> 01:21:26,260
- You'll use it all up.
- No more advances on what you ain't done.

851
01:21:26,553 --> 01:21:31,140
Sweetheart, we're just waiting
on this weather to clear!

852
01:21:31,433 --> 01:21:35,019
We're going to need more food!
About three days' worth.

853
01:21:35,562 --> 01:21:36,979
Three days?

854
01:21:38,023 --> 01:21:39,606
We can kill them tomorrow.

855
01:21:39,816 --> 01:21:43,986
- I don't kill nobody without him.
- We don't need him! We can do it.

856
01:21:44,237 --> 01:21:45,571
Besides...

857
01:21:45,905 --> 01:21:49,158
... he ain't nothing
but a broken-down pig farmer.

858
01:21:49,325 --> 01:21:52,536
We'll bring food in the morning,
and some whiskey too!

859
01:21:52,787 --> 01:21:56,040
And some medicine if you got any!

860
01:21:56,541 --> 01:21:59,001
Don't it make you sick hearing him?

861
01:21:59,169 --> 01:22:00,794
Don't you ladies worry!

862
01:22:02,047 --> 01:22:06,592
Me and Ned, we'll kill them two
sons of bitches for you!

863
01:22:12,348 --> 01:22:13,807
Claudia.

864
01:22:22,609 --> 01:22:25,652
- Claudia's not here.
- Is that you, Ned?

865
01:22:27,572 --> 01:22:28,947
I seen him.

866
01:22:32,077 --> 01:22:34,286
I seen the Angel of Death.

867
01:22:34,871 --> 01:22:37,372
I seen a river, Ned.

868
01:22:38,374 --> 01:22:42,628
- He's got snake eyes.
- Who's got snake eyes?

869
01:22:43,088 --> 01:22:44,880
It's the Angel of Death.

870
01:22:49,219 --> 01:22:51,095
I'm scared of dying.

871
01:22:51,721 --> 01:22:53,514
Easy, partner.

872
01:22:54,140 --> 01:22:56,016
I seen Claudia too.

873
01:22:56,893 --> 01:23:00,145
That's good you saw Claudia, ain't it?

874
01:23:00,647 --> 01:23:03,232
Her face was all covered with worms.

875
01:23:04,109 --> 01:23:05,692
Ned, I'm scared.

876
01:23:06,903 --> 01:23:08,362
I'm dying.

877
01:23:12,325 --> 01:23:15,369
You won't--
No, don't tell nobody.

878
01:23:15,829 --> 01:23:17,746
Don't tell my kids...

879
01:23:18,331 --> 01:23:22,167
... none of the things I done.
You hear me?

880
01:23:22,919 --> 01:23:24,253
All right, Will.

881
01:23:41,688 --> 01:23:43,564
He's gonna die, ain't he?

882
01:23:45,066 --> 01:23:46,441
Maybe.

883
01:23:46,860 --> 01:23:49,027
Supposing he does?

884
01:23:52,782 --> 01:23:54,199
We'll bury him.

885
01:23:54,450 --> 01:23:56,285
That ain't what I mean.

886
01:24:00,039 --> 01:24:03,625
You mean, will I help
you kill them cowboys?

887
01:24:04,669 --> 01:24:06,712
I can't spot them myself.

888
01:24:07,172 --> 01:24:08,672
But you could.

889
01:24:09,257 --> 01:24:13,385
That big bastard, you could spot him
a half-mile off, I bet.

890
01:24:14,804 --> 01:24:16,471
And if I spot him?

891
01:24:17,724 --> 01:24:20,225
Then I ride up close and shoot him.

892
01:24:23,188 --> 01:24:24,438
Just like that?

893
01:24:24,898 --> 01:24:27,482
I'm a damn killer.
I done it before.

894
01:24:30,486 --> 01:24:32,738
I'm more of a killer than he is.

895
01:24:34,908 --> 01:24:36,158
Yeah?

896
01:25:02,518 --> 01:25:05,604
I thought you was an angel.

897
01:25:06,481 --> 01:25:08,023
You ain't dead.

898
01:25:16,366 --> 01:25:17,950
Some big fellow...

899
01:25:19,035 --> 01:25:21,161
... kicked the hell out of me.

900
01:25:24,040 --> 01:25:26,291
I must look like you now.

901
01:25:28,378 --> 01:25:30,629
You don't look nothing like me.

902
01:25:32,548 --> 01:25:34,174
No offense meant.

903
01:25:37,011 --> 01:25:40,347
You got to be the one
those cowboys cut up.

904
01:25:46,396 --> 01:25:49,022
My partners, Ned and that Kid...

905
01:25:49,565 --> 01:25:51,275
... they around?

906
01:25:52,068 --> 01:25:55,153
They went out scouting
when your fever broke.

907
01:25:56,072 --> 01:25:57,197
Scouting?

908
01:25:58,074 --> 01:26:00,033
Out to the Bar T...

909
01:26:00,410 --> 01:26:02,327
... looking for them.

910
01:26:06,416 --> 01:26:08,208
How long I been here?

911
01:26:09,419 --> 01:26:10,836
Three days.

912
01:26:12,422 --> 01:26:14,047
Are you hungry or... ?

913
01:26:14,757 --> 01:26:16,550
Three days?

914
01:26:16,801 --> 01:26:18,343
I ought to be... .

915
01:26:30,606 --> 01:26:33,025
I thought I was gone.

916
01:26:35,611 --> 01:26:39,740
I wouldn't normally pay no notice
to high country like this...

917
01:26:40,575 --> 01:26:43,118
... trees,
but I'm sure noticing now.

918
01:26:44,120 --> 01:26:46,621
Thought I was dying for sure.

919
01:26:48,458 --> 01:26:50,083
I brought your hat.

920
01:26:50,418 --> 01:26:52,961
You left it down at Greely's.

921
01:26:53,629 --> 01:26:54,963
Thanks.

922
01:26:56,841 --> 01:26:58,216
That sheriff... .

923
01:26:59,469 --> 01:27:02,220
- He still looking for me?
- Little Bill?

924
01:27:02,472 --> 01:27:05,223
No, he thinks you went south.

925
01:27:08,478 --> 01:27:11,355
Are you really gonna
kill them cowboys?

926
01:27:12,482 --> 01:27:13,774
I guess.

927
01:27:14,609 --> 01:27:17,069
Still a payment coming, isn't there?

928
01:27:18,654 --> 01:27:21,406
Them other two, your friends...

929
01:27:21,949 --> 01:27:24,993
... they been taking
advances on the payment.

930
01:27:25,828 --> 01:27:27,245
Advances?

931
01:27:29,165 --> 01:27:32,292
- Free ones.
- Free ones?

932
01:27:33,169 --> 01:27:36,088
Alice and Silky been
giving them free ones.

933
01:27:38,007 --> 01:27:39,257
I see.

934
01:27:43,012 --> 01:27:45,097
Would you like a free one?

935
01:27:53,356 --> 01:27:56,650
No. I guess not.

936
01:27:57,443 --> 01:28:01,113
I didn't mean with me.
I meant...

937
01:28:01,364 --> 01:28:06,034
... Alice and Silky would be happy
to give you a free one if you wanted.

938
01:28:06,202 --> 01:28:08,453
That's all I meant.

939
01:28:09,831 --> 01:28:12,207
I didn't mean...

940
01:28:12,500 --> 01:28:16,545
... I didn't want a free one
because you been cut up and all.

941
01:28:17,547 --> 01:28:21,299
What I said about you looking like me,
that ain't true.

942
01:28:21,884 --> 01:28:23,718
You ain't ugly like me.

943
01:28:25,179 --> 01:28:28,682
It's just that we both got scars.

944
01:28:30,852 --> 01:28:34,354
You're a beautiful woman,
and if I wanted a free one...

945
01:28:34,730 --> 01:28:38,233
... I'd want it with you
more than the other two.

946
01:28:40,570 --> 01:28:41,987
It's just that...

947
01:28:42,738 --> 01:28:45,157
... I can't on account of my wife.

948
01:28:51,747 --> 01:28:52,998
Your wife?

949
01:28:53,916 --> 01:28:57,377
Yeah. You see?

950
01:29:02,091 --> 01:29:03,925
I admire you for that.

951
01:29:04,594 --> 01:29:07,053
For being true to your wife.

952
01:29:08,097 --> 01:29:10,223
I've known a lot of men...

953
01:29:12,477 --> 01:29:13,894
... who weren't.

954
01:29:16,272 --> 01:29:17,731
I suppose.

955
01:29:24,238 --> 01:29:26,031
Is she back in Kansas?

956
01:29:27,950 --> 01:29:29,201
Yeah.

957
01:29:30,244 --> 01:29:32,913
She's watching over my young ones.

958
01:29:38,461 --> 01:29:41,254
- Hang on!
- Get the damn iron!

959
01:29:51,057 --> 01:29:52,807
Jesus, fellas!

960
01:30:04,779 --> 01:30:06,947
Jesus, boys, my leg's broke!

961
01:30:08,991 --> 01:30:10,575
I'm pinned, boys!

962
01:30:11,994 --> 01:30:13,620
Better finish him, Ned.

963
01:30:14,038 --> 01:30:16,164
He ain't dead? You didn't get him?

964
01:30:16,457 --> 01:30:18,333
He got the boy's horse.

965
01:30:19,043 --> 01:30:21,419
Finish him before he gets clear.

966
01:30:24,173 --> 01:30:26,091
Get behind them rocks.

967
01:30:26,842 --> 01:30:28,134
Get over there!

968
01:30:31,514 --> 01:30:35,642
What happened? He ain't killed?!
What's going on?

969
01:30:36,018 --> 01:30:38,478
He gets in those rocks,
we won't get him.

970
01:30:38,854 --> 01:30:41,314
- Unless we go down there.
- What rocks?

971
01:30:41,691 --> 01:30:44,484
Why don't you shoot?
What's going on?

972
01:30:49,448 --> 01:30:50,490
Shoot!

973
01:31:04,088 --> 01:31:06,464
I ain't very good with one of these.

974
01:31:12,096 --> 01:31:14,514
Keep going, Davey! The rocks!

975
01:31:16,726 --> 01:31:18,059
Did you get him?

976
01:31:18,894 --> 01:31:20,145
Where is he?

977
01:31:20,396 --> 01:31:27,485
How many more shots do I have?

978
01:31:31,032 --> 01:31:34,326
- Two.
- Two.

979
01:31:43,878 --> 01:31:45,337
Did you get him?

980
01:32:02,647 --> 01:32:04,564
Here, reload this.

981
01:32:05,775 --> 01:32:08,068
- You missed him.
- I got him.

982
01:32:09,111 --> 01:32:11,946
They shot me, boys.

983
01:32:12,114 --> 01:32:13,406
He ain't killed.

984
01:32:14,116 --> 01:32:15,867
Maybe, maybe not.

985
01:32:16,452 --> 01:32:18,703
Got him through the gut, I think.

986
01:32:23,125 --> 01:32:24,751
Think he'll die?

987
01:32:27,171 --> 01:32:29,756
You think we killed him?

988
01:32:36,555 --> 01:32:37,931
Yeah.

989
01:32:39,183 --> 01:32:42,477
We killed him, I guess.

990
01:32:46,148 --> 01:32:48,066
I'm dying, boys!

991
01:32:48,776 --> 01:32:52,404
Then you shouldn't have cut up
no woman, you asshole!

992
01:32:57,993 --> 01:33:00,704
Jesus, I'm so thirsty!

993
01:33:03,499 --> 01:33:06,751
Give me some water, please!

994
01:33:07,169 --> 01:33:08,503
Please, Slim!

995
01:33:09,672 --> 01:33:11,297
I'm bleeding, Slim!

996
01:33:15,511 --> 01:33:18,263
Give him a drink of water,
goddamn it!

997
01:33:22,351 --> 01:33:26,438
Give him some water, for chrissake!
We ain't gonna shoot!

998
01:33:28,482 --> 01:33:31,735
- You ain't gonna shoot?
- No.

999
01:33:33,863 --> 01:33:35,613
Hold on, Davey-boy!

1000
01:33:36,866 --> 01:33:38,324
Here I come now!

1001
01:33:44,874 --> 01:33:46,833
Don't shoot me,
you bastards!

1002
01:33:50,379 --> 01:33:51,671
Shit!

1003
01:34:01,557 --> 01:34:03,183
They take him water?

1004
01:34:05,895 --> 01:34:08,188
Jesus, Johnny! They shot him!

1005
01:34:08,397 --> 01:34:10,023
Hold on now!

1006
01:34:18,783 --> 01:34:22,327
You murdering bastards!
You killed our Davey-boy!

1007
01:34:31,253 --> 01:34:33,087
When will we double back?

1008
01:34:33,798 --> 01:34:35,548
After a ways.

1009
01:34:36,926 --> 01:34:38,176
Not me.

1010
01:34:38,928 --> 01:34:44,265
- I'm heading back down to Kansas.
- We got to kill the other one first.

1011
01:34:44,433 --> 01:34:48,561
With any luck, we'll find him
by nightfall or in the morning.

1012
01:34:48,729 --> 01:34:52,607
We'll shoot him and head back
with the money.

1013
01:34:53,776 --> 01:34:56,945
- Do you want the Spencer?
- It's no time to quit.

1014
01:34:57,238 --> 01:34:59,697
- You'll lose your share.
- Shut up!

1015
01:34:59,949 --> 01:35:02,700
I'll see you, Will.
So long, Kid.

1016
01:35:11,168 --> 01:35:14,754
Here. I ain't no good
with that damn thing.

1017
01:35:15,256 --> 01:35:19,968
Me and the Kid'll head over
to that ranch and we'll shoot him.

1018
01:35:20,427 --> 01:35:24,305
We'll meet up with you,
get our money, and go back together.

1019
01:35:24,932 --> 01:35:27,392
Suppose he don't go back
to the ranch?

1020
01:35:27,768 --> 01:35:31,771
He ain't going into town
or stay out in the open country.

1021
01:35:32,106 --> 01:35:34,065
He'll hole up at that ranch.

1022
01:35:35,943 --> 01:35:37,402
I ain't waiting.

1023
01:35:37,945 --> 01:35:40,530
I'll look in on your young ones.

1024
01:35:47,288 --> 01:35:50,290
Forget what the Kid said
about the money.

1025
01:35:50,499 --> 01:35:53,042
I'll bring your share.

1026
01:35:55,838 --> 01:35:57,422
Kid's full of shit.

1027
01:36:25,618 --> 01:36:27,827
Just doing some repairs up here.

1028
01:36:28,203 --> 01:36:30,038
They killed one of them cowboys.

1029
01:36:34,126 --> 01:36:35,376
Shit!

1030
01:36:36,879 --> 01:36:41,424
Parson said he saw three men,
right after sunup, headed east.

1031
01:36:41,675 --> 01:36:46,137
One was on a dun and another
was on a flea-bitten gray.

1032
01:36:46,722 --> 01:36:50,975
He didn't know what the third one
was on, maybe an appaloosa.

1033
01:36:51,226 --> 01:36:55,313
Amos says to ask if the county
will pay for feed for all the horses.

1034
01:36:55,564 --> 01:36:58,858
Witherspoon won't sell us
no more shells without pay.

1035
01:36:59,109 --> 01:37:00,735
Hell, use my dogs!

1036
01:37:00,986 --> 01:37:03,237
Then the county's got
to be responsible.

1037
01:37:04,114 --> 01:37:08,660
Get on out there to the Bar T
and make sure that other cowboy...

1038
01:37:08,911 --> 01:37:11,496
... stays put
and don't expose himself.

1039
01:37:21,507 --> 01:37:23,841
I didn't think they'd really do it.

1040
01:37:24,468 --> 01:37:27,345
Think they come up
from Kansas to fuck us?

1041
01:37:30,724 --> 01:37:34,102
That Kid, he's just a boy
and the other one...

1042
01:37:34,353 --> 01:37:37,230
... Will, the nice one,
being so true to his wife... .

1043
01:37:37,481 --> 01:37:40,024
Wife?
He ain't got no wife.

1044
01:37:40,526 --> 01:37:43,361
- Yes, he does. He--
- He ain't got no wife.

1045
01:37:43,862 --> 01:37:45,697
Not above ground, anyways.

1046
01:37:51,787 --> 01:37:53,204
Murdering whores!

1047
01:37:54,373 --> 01:37:57,792
He had it coming!
He had it coming for what he done!

1048
01:37:58,127 --> 01:38:01,963
And the other one too!
Both of them for what they done!

1049
01:38:12,141 --> 01:38:13,558
We got one!

1050
01:38:15,978 --> 01:38:18,646
We got one, sheriff!
Out by Cow Creek!

1051
01:38:18,981 --> 01:38:21,357
- Is he alive?
- Hell, yeah!

1052
01:38:21,608 --> 01:38:26,237
Bunch of us from Bar T went looking
because they killed one of our own.

1053
01:38:26,572 --> 01:38:29,741
Come across the bastard
on a roan heading south.

1054
01:38:30,075 --> 01:38:31,325
He admit it?

1055
01:38:31,660 --> 01:38:35,747
No. But I guess he will soon enough.
Had a Spencer rifle on him.

1056
01:38:36,498 --> 01:38:37,999
They messing him up?

1057
01:38:39,585 --> 01:38:41,085
Little bit.

1058
01:38:44,757 --> 01:38:48,760
Get out there. Find out what happened
to those other two!

1059
01:39:11,867 --> 01:39:14,035
See anything out there, Buck?

1060
01:39:14,286 --> 01:39:18,122
Hell, yes!
Seen about 200 fellows packing rifles.

1061
01:39:18,373 --> 01:39:22,668
Got the place surrounded.
Say they want Quick Mike's ass.

1062
01:39:22,920 --> 01:39:26,214
I said, "How much?" They says, "Five. "
I said, "Dollars?"

1063
01:39:26,465 --> 01:39:27,715
They said, "Cents. "

1064
01:39:27,966 --> 01:39:29,467
I said, "Sold. "

1065
01:39:31,136 --> 01:39:32,804
Well, I ain't worried!

1066
01:39:33,138 --> 01:39:36,641
Because I got me some protection.

1067
01:40:01,166 --> 01:40:03,459
- Tell you where them others is?
- Nope.

1068
01:40:03,627 --> 01:40:07,421
- Any names?
- Only told us his name, Ned Roundtree.

1069
01:40:10,008 --> 01:40:11,259
Bring him in.

1070
01:40:14,263 --> 01:40:17,932
You'll want to tell me
and Mr. Beauchamp here...

1071
01:40:18,100 --> 01:40:20,309
... all about your two friends.

1072
01:40:20,727 --> 01:40:26,065
I'll want the names and whereabouts
of those son of a bitches.

1073
01:40:39,746 --> 01:40:41,372
Sure is ripe.

1074
01:40:43,041 --> 01:40:44,876
Going to get a lot riper.

1075
01:40:46,295 --> 01:40:47,879
Think he's still in there?

1076
01:40:49,464 --> 01:40:51,132
He's in there.

1077
01:40:51,967 --> 01:40:55,803
He's holding on to his shit
like it was money.

1078
01:40:55,971 --> 01:40:57,388
He's in there.

1079
01:40:57,890 --> 01:41:01,225
Tell me right off if you see him.

1080
01:41:02,477 --> 01:41:04,896
You won't shoot him your own self?

1081
01:41:05,063 --> 01:41:07,773
You can shoot him.

1082
01:41:44,394 --> 01:41:47,438
Now you and Mr. Quincy and... .

1083
01:41:47,689 --> 01:41:50,149
What was the young fellow's name?

1084
01:41:53,904 --> 01:41:55,488
Elroy Tate.

1085
01:42:00,369 --> 01:42:02,703
No, that's not what you said.

1086
01:42:03,163 --> 01:42:06,123
- Hell if it ain't!
- No, you said:

1087
01:42:06,708 --> 01:42:09,460
"Elroy Quincy out of Medicine Hat...

1088
01:42:11,213 --> 01:42:13,965
... and Henry Tate out of Cheyenne. "

1089
01:42:14,466 --> 01:42:18,302
Hell if I did.

1090
01:42:20,514 --> 01:42:23,849
Go get them whores that pumped
these boys that night.

1091
01:42:24,101 --> 01:42:26,143
Strawberry Alice and Silky?

1092
01:42:26,478 --> 01:42:28,145
Go on and get them!

1093
01:42:37,197 --> 01:42:41,409
Them whores are going to tell
different lies than you.

1094
01:42:42,661 --> 01:42:47,456
And when their lies
ain't the same as your lies... .

1095
01:42:48,166 --> 01:42:50,376
Well, I ain't going to hurt no woman.

1096
01:42:51,503 --> 01:42:53,462
But I'm going to hurt you.

1097
01:42:55,924 --> 01:42:58,092
Not gentle like before...

1098
01:42:59,636 --> 01:43:01,387
... but bad.

1099
01:43:17,654 --> 01:43:19,113
Where you going?

1100
01:43:19,281 --> 01:43:21,449
- The shithouse.
- Let me finish.

1101
01:43:21,783 --> 01:43:24,035
To protect me while I take a dump?

1102
01:43:24,286 --> 01:43:26,454
- You'll get bushwhacked.
- I'll fart on them.

1103
01:43:26,705 --> 01:43:29,874
- I'll go.
- Yeah, you can wipe my ass, Thirsty.

1104
01:43:30,125 --> 01:43:34,003
Hell with him. He ain't polite,
he should get shot.

1105
01:43:37,466 --> 01:43:38,799
Is that him?

1106
01:43:39,051 --> 01:43:40,676
Yeah, that's him.

1107
01:43:44,473 --> 01:43:48,351
All right, Kid. Go get him.
He's all yours.

1108
01:44:23,845 --> 01:44:24,970
Assassins!

1109
01:44:28,975 --> 01:44:30,351
Shoot him!

1110
01:44:45,992 --> 01:44:47,535
Come on, goddamn it!

1111
01:45:04,636 --> 01:45:06,053
Did you get him?

1112
01:45:18,942 --> 01:45:20,025
Cover me.

1113
01:45:22,571 --> 01:45:24,947
- I can't see them!
- Just shoot!

1114
01:46:02,027 --> 01:46:04,612
Was it like that in the old days?

1115
01:46:05,280 --> 01:46:07,823
Everybody riding out, shooting...

1116
01:46:08,283 --> 01:46:12,203
... smoke all over, folks yelling,
bullets whizzing by?

1117
01:46:14,039 --> 01:46:15,372
I guess so.

1118
01:46:19,461 --> 01:46:21,962
Shit, I thought they'd get us.

1119
01:46:23,131 --> 01:46:25,132
I was even scared a little.

1120
01:46:25,467 --> 01:46:26,717
For a minute.

1121
01:46:29,471 --> 01:46:31,472
You ever scared in them days?

1122
01:46:33,725 --> 01:46:35,142
I can't remember.

1123
01:46:36,478 --> 01:46:39,522
I was drunk most of the time.

1124
01:46:45,403 --> 01:46:47,988
I shot that fucker three times!

1125
01:46:49,491 --> 01:46:53,410
He was taking a shit,
went for his pistol and I blazed away.

1126
01:46:53,578 --> 01:46:54,954
First shot...

1127
01:46:56,748 --> 01:46:58,958
... I got him right in the chest.

1128
01:47:02,671 --> 01:47:05,714
- Say, Will?
- Yeah?

1129
01:47:08,176 --> 01:47:09,760
That was the first one.

1130
01:47:11,179 --> 01:47:12,555
First one what?

1131
01:47:14,933 --> 01:47:16,767
First one I ever killed.

1132
01:47:18,311 --> 01:47:19,395
Yeah?

1133
01:47:20,772 --> 01:47:23,190
You know how I said I shot five men?

1134
01:47:24,609 --> 01:47:26,193
It weren't true.

1135
01:47:28,613 --> 01:47:31,907
That Mexican with the knife?

1136
01:47:32,117 --> 01:47:36,453
I just busted his leg with a shovel.
I didn't kill him or nothing.

1137
01:47:39,749 --> 01:47:43,085
You sure killed
the hell out of that fellow today.

1138
01:47:44,921 --> 01:47:46,505
Hell, yeah!

1139
01:47:49,968 --> 01:47:52,970
Killed the hell out of him, didn't l?

1140
01:47:53,221 --> 01:47:56,265
Three shots and he was taking a shit.

1141
01:48:02,814 --> 01:48:04,189
Take a drink, Kid.

1142
01:48:15,076 --> 01:48:16,952
Jesus Christ!

1143
01:48:29,424 --> 01:48:31,300
It don't seem real.

1144
01:48:32,844 --> 01:48:35,971
How he ain't gonna
never breath again, ever.

1145
01:48:36,931 --> 01:48:38,265
How he's dead.

1146
01:48:40,101 --> 01:48:42,686
And the other one too.

1147
01:48:44,481 --> 01:48:47,775
On account of pulling a trigger.

1148
01:48:49,694 --> 01:48:52,988
It's a hell of a thing, killing a man.

1149
01:48:54,199 --> 01:48:57,034
You take away all he's got...

1150
01:48:57,202 --> 01:48:59,411
... and all he's ever gonna have.

1151
01:49:04,876 --> 01:49:06,877
I guess they had it coming.

1152
01:49:12,884 --> 01:49:15,135
We all have it coming, Kid.

1153
01:49:29,734 --> 01:49:32,653
I was watching
that you weren't followed.

1154
01:49:34,072 --> 01:49:39,284
Silky and Faith rode off to the east
and two deputies followed them.

1155
01:49:44,999 --> 01:49:48,544
- You want to help me count this?
- I trust you.

1156
01:49:48,795 --> 01:49:51,213
Don't go trusting me too much.

1157
01:49:52,090 --> 01:49:55,426
In fact, we'll give Ned his share
together.

1158
01:49:55,677 --> 01:49:58,303
You'll know I ain't holding out on you.

1159
01:49:58,555 --> 01:49:59,930
Ned's share?

1160
01:50:02,892 --> 01:50:04,935
He went south.
We'll catch up.

1161
01:50:05,687 --> 01:50:07,479
He's dead.

1162
01:50:10,859 --> 01:50:13,444
What do you mean, dead?

1163
01:50:13,611 --> 01:50:16,405
He went south yesterday.
He ain't dead.

1164
01:50:16,948 --> 01:50:19,533
They killed him.
I thought you knew.

1165
01:50:19,826 --> 01:50:21,702
Nobody killed Ned!

1166
01:50:21,953 --> 01:50:24,663
He didn't kill anyone.
He went south!

1167
01:50:24,831 --> 01:50:26,915
Why would anybody kill Ned?

1168
01:50:29,502 --> 01:50:30,753
Who killed him?

1169
01:50:31,546 --> 01:50:32,796
Little Bill.

1170
01:50:33,131 --> 01:50:35,632
The Bar T boys caught him...

1171
01:50:36,009 --> 01:50:38,051
... and Little Bill beat him up.

1172
01:50:38,219 --> 01:50:43,140
He was making him answer questions,
beating him up. Then Ned just died.

1173
01:50:43,475 --> 01:50:46,018
They got a sign on him
says he was a killer.

1174
01:50:46,186 --> 01:50:47,644
A sign on him?

1175
01:50:48,396 --> 01:50:49,980
In front of Greely's.

1176
01:50:50,315 --> 01:50:52,566
A sign on him in front of Greely's!

1177
01:50:56,988 --> 01:51:00,282
These questions he was asking...

1178
01:51:00,450 --> 01:51:02,701
... what kind were they?

1179
01:51:05,455 --> 01:51:08,832
About where you and him was.

1180
01:51:09,250 --> 01:51:10,501
Then what?

1181
01:51:11,586 --> 01:51:15,923
A cowboy come in saying you killed
Quick Mike in the shithouse.

1182
01:51:16,925 --> 01:51:19,802
So Little Bill killed him
for what we done?

1183
01:51:20,053 --> 01:51:21,428
Not on purpose.

1184
01:51:22,347 --> 01:51:26,350
But he started hurting him worse.
Making him tell stuff.

1185
01:51:26,684 --> 01:51:28,227
First, Ned wouldn't talk.

1186
01:51:29,020 --> 01:51:33,899
Then Little Bill hurt him so bad,
he said who you was.

1187
01:51:34,859 --> 01:51:38,987
He said how you was really
William Munny out of Missouri.

1188
01:51:39,155 --> 01:51:42,157
Little Bill said, "The one
who dynamited...

1189
01:51:42,408 --> 01:51:45,744
... the railroad in '69,
killing women and children?"

1190
01:51:45,912 --> 01:51:49,039
Ned said you done a lot worse.
Said you was...

1191
01:51:49,290 --> 01:51:52,960
... more cold-blooded than Will Bonney.
Said if he hurt Ned again...

1192
01:51:53,211 --> 01:51:58,298
... you'd come kill him
like you killed a U. S. marshal in '70.

1193
01:52:03,054 --> 01:52:06,265
That didn't scare him, did it?

1194
01:52:07,225 --> 01:52:08,851
No, sir.

1195
01:52:16,484 --> 01:52:18,318
Give me your Schofield.

1196
01:52:18,570 --> 01:52:19,987
What for, Will?

1197
01:52:20,154 --> 01:52:24,032
- Give it to me.
- Yeah. Sure.

1198
01:52:28,621 --> 01:52:30,414
You want it, keep it.

1199
01:52:30,665 --> 01:52:32,040
I won't use it.

1200
01:52:34,627 --> 01:52:36,712
I won't kill nobody no more.

1201
01:52:40,300 --> 01:52:41,925
I ain't like you, Will.

1202
01:52:45,972 --> 01:52:49,099
You better ride on back, miss.

1203
01:52:52,645 --> 01:52:55,230
Go on, keep all of it.
It's yours.

1204
01:52:56,107 --> 01:52:58,984
What about spectacles
and fancy clothes?

1205
01:53:00,069 --> 01:53:03,071
I'd rather be blind and ragged
than dead.

1206
01:53:04,449 --> 01:53:08,410
You don't have to worry, Kid.
I ain't going to kill you.

1207
01:53:08,912 --> 01:53:10,996
You're the only friend I got.

1208
01:53:18,922 --> 01:53:23,467
Take this money and give my half
and Ned's half to my kids.

1209
01:53:24,052 --> 01:53:27,596
Tell them if I ain't back in a week,
to give half to Sally.

1210
01:53:27,847 --> 01:53:30,557
You keep the rest.
Get them spectacles.

1211
01:53:30,808 --> 01:53:32,559
You'll go kill Little Bill?

1212
01:53:33,019 --> 01:53:37,105
Stay clear of folks you see.
There'll be a lot out to hang you.

1213
01:53:37,690 --> 01:53:38,982
Get going.

1214
01:54:22,777 --> 01:54:27,030
I'll say this just one more time,
so don't ask me again!

1215
01:54:27,198 --> 01:54:32,869
Those on today's posse got one drink
coming from the county budget!

1216
01:54:33,830 --> 01:54:37,124
And those who rode yesterday
get one for that too.

1217
01:54:38,418 --> 01:54:39,960
Hold it!

1218
01:54:40,211 --> 01:54:44,673
That's two! After that, it comes
out of your own pocket! You hear?

1219
01:54:44,924 --> 01:54:47,968
- Yes, sir.
- We'll pull out early in the morning.

1220
01:54:48,386 --> 01:54:52,764
We'll chase them clear to Texas,
so don't spend too much money.

1221
01:54:53,725 --> 01:54:56,351
We'll divide up into four parties!

1222
01:54:56,602 --> 01:55:00,564
We'll hit all the farms and trails
in a big circle.

1223
01:55:00,815 --> 01:55:05,152
We're bound to find somebody
who's seen these skunks.

1224
01:55:22,587 --> 01:55:24,838
Who owns this shithole?

1225
01:55:34,348 --> 01:55:37,726
You, fat man. Speak up.

1226
01:55:40,354 --> 01:55:42,814
I own this establishment.

1227
01:55:45,276 --> 01:55:48,945
I bought it from Greely for $1000.

1228
01:55:50,364 --> 01:55:51,990
Better clear out.

1229
01:55:54,952 --> 01:55:57,913
Hold it!

1230
01:56:07,131 --> 01:56:10,217
Sir, you are a cowardly
son of a bitch!

1231
01:56:11,219 --> 01:56:13,178
You just shot an unarmed man.

1232
01:56:13,638 --> 01:56:15,680
He should've armed himself...

1233
01:56:15,932 --> 01:56:18,683
... if he's going to decorate his saloon
with my friend.

1234
01:56:19,393 --> 01:56:22,229
You'd be William Munny
out of Missouri...

1235
01:56:22,396 --> 01:56:24,397
... killer of women and children.

1236
01:56:25,066 --> 01:56:26,483
That's right.

1237
01:56:28,194 --> 01:56:30,153
I killed women and children.

1238
01:56:31,697 --> 01:56:35,575
Killed just about everything
that walks or crawls.

1239
01:56:36,828 --> 01:56:39,496
And I'm here to kill you, Little Bill.

1240
01:56:40,331 --> 01:56:42,666
For what you did to Ned.

1241
01:56:46,838 --> 01:56:48,755
You boys better move away.

1242
01:56:59,225 --> 01:57:03,395
All right, gentlemen.
He's got one barrel left.

1243
01:57:04,272 --> 01:57:06,439
When he fires it,
use your pistols...

1244
01:57:06,691 --> 01:57:10,944
... and shoot him down
like the mangy scoundrel he is!

1245
01:57:24,041 --> 01:57:26,501
Misfire! Kill the son of a bitch!

1246
01:58:03,331 --> 01:58:07,459
Any man don't want to get killed,
better clear on out the back.

1247
01:58:52,129 --> 01:58:53,797
I'm shot! I'm shot!

1248
01:58:54,298 --> 01:58:55,632
You ain't shot.

1249
01:59:01,681 --> 01:59:04,641
I don't have a gun.
I am not armed.

1250
01:59:06,060 --> 01:59:07,560
Pick up that rifle.

1251
01:59:09,522 --> 01:59:10,814
Pick it up.

1252
01:59:13,192 --> 01:59:14,276
Shells too.

1253
01:59:27,498 --> 01:59:28,957
You killed Little Bill.

1254
01:59:30,501 --> 01:59:32,002
Sure you ain't armed?

1255
01:59:34,422 --> 01:59:36,339
I'm not.
I don't have a gun.

1256
01:59:36,590 --> 01:59:39,301
I've never had a gun.
I'm a writer!

1257
01:59:40,761 --> 01:59:42,262
A writer?

1258
01:59:43,055 --> 01:59:45,181
- Letters and such?
- Books.

1259
01:59:45,891 --> 01:59:47,434
Books.

1260
01:59:47,601 --> 01:59:51,521
I don't believe it, you killed five men.
Single-handed.

1261
02:00:00,114 --> 02:00:03,074
- That's a Spencer rifle, right?
- Right.

1262
02:00:11,250 --> 02:00:12,667
Who'd you kill first?

1263
02:00:16,589 --> 02:00:18,840
"When confronted by superior numbers...

1264
02:00:19,091 --> 02:00:23,136
... an experienced gunfighter will
fire on the best shot first. "

1265
02:00:23,304 --> 02:00:27,640
Little Bill said that.
You probably killed him first.

1266
02:00:27,808 --> 02:00:29,851
I was lucky in the order.

1267
02:00:30,811 --> 02:00:34,814
I'm always lucky
when it comes to killing folks.

1268
02:00:35,691 --> 02:00:39,444
That so? Who was next?
Clyde, right?

1269
02:00:39,695 --> 02:00:42,405
You killed Clyde,
or it was Deputy Andy--

1270
02:00:42,656 --> 02:00:45,283
All I can tell you is,
who'll be last.

1271
02:01:21,946 --> 02:01:23,905
I don't deserve this.

1272
02:01:25,950 --> 02:01:27,534
To die like this.

1273
02:01:30,371 --> 02:01:32,455
I was building a house.

1274
02:01:33,374 --> 02:01:36,042
got nothing to do with it.

1275
02:01:38,754 --> 02:01:42,173
I'll see you in hell, William Munny.

1276
02:01:48,597 --> 02:01:50,014
Yeah.

1277
02:02:21,505 --> 02:02:23,631
All right, I'm coming out!

1278
02:02:24,049 --> 02:02:26,843
Any man I see out there, I'll kill him!

1279
02:02:27,428 --> 02:02:29,929
Anyone takes a shot at me...

1280
02:02:30,639 --> 02:02:35,477
... I'm not only going to kill him,
but his wife and all his friends.

1281
02:02:35,811 --> 02:02:38,062
And burn his damn house down!

1282
02:02:45,404 --> 02:02:47,197
Nobody better shoot!

1283
02:03:02,755 --> 02:03:04,839
Charley, go ahead.
Shoot him!

1284
02:03:18,979 --> 02:03:20,313
I can't.

1285
02:03:20,773 --> 02:03:23,566
Hell, no!
I ain't no deputy!

1286
02:03:43,462 --> 02:03:46,089
You better bury Ned right!

1287
02:03:46,674 --> 02:03:50,385
You better not cut up
nor otherwise harm no whores!

1288
02:03:54,306 --> 02:03:58,685
Or I'll come back and kill every
one of you sons of bitches.

1289
02:10:36,500 --> 02:10:38,501
[ENGLISH]

